Voting begins for the second stage of New Zealand's flag referendum with the current flag going up against the design chosen on the first stage of the referendum. Voting will end on March 23 with polling showing the current flag is favoured to win. (BBC) (CNN)New York businessman Donald Trump wins the Republican Party primary while Vermont Senator Bernie Sanders wins the Democratic Party primary. (NBC News) This makes Sanders the first Jewish and the first self-described democratic socialist to win a U.S. presidential primary. (The Week) (CNN) (The Huffington Post) Barry Goldwater, the 1964 Republican presidential nominee, was the first winner of Jewish heritage, but was a Christian. (CNN)